(1287, 'Christine Boissarie', 'ATM INTERNATIONALE', 'christine.boissarie@atm-interntionale.com', '00971505039606', 'MENA UITP', 'Dubai', '48', '40000', '1', 'Hi! \r\nWe are going to exhibit at the MENA Transport Congress and Exhibition (MTCE) which will take place from 28 February till 1 March 2024 and I would like to receive from your company a budgetary proposal for a custom-made stand.\r\nPlease find attached the floor map. Our space is the 5C50, hence 48 m2 in total (LUMIPLAN/CIBEST/ATM).\r\nThe stand will actually be used by 3 companies:\r\n- ourselves, ATM INTERNATIONALE, a French company with a branch office in Abu dhabi since 2012 providing ITS (intelligent transport systems) solutions and related technical support/maintenance in the UAE, KSA and Bahrain for the public transportation sector (public transport operators and authorities). Our main clients in the UAE are the RTA and ITC (Integrated Transport Center) in Abu Dhabi. \r\n- LUMIPLAN, a French manufacturer of digital communication solutions for public transport. LUMIPLAN manufactures Real time passengers informations systems, destinations signs for buses, etc\r\n- CIBEST Group, a French manufacturer of IT managed solutions for public transportation (onboard cctv video monitoring systems for buses, passenger counting systems, etc).\r\n\r\nBecause we are sharing this space, we want to appear as LUMIPLAN/CIBEST/ATM. It will be the name of our booth and our commercial name in the catalogue of the exhibition. So that\'s the name that should appear on the top of our booth.\r\n\r\nWe want to display some equipment. We are going to bring from France :\r\n- TFT screens\r\n- LED Destination sign (which is up to 190 cm wide and weighs around 12 kg)\r\n- a standalone interactive totem (something similar to what you can find in malls to help shoppers to find their way)\r\n- roll-ups\r\n\r\nWe will need of course also tables and chairs and other furniture + electrical connectors.\r\n\r\nIn terms of design, please find attached some pictures of our booth at a former exhibition. We want something simple but elegant, mostly open, bright and white.\r\n\r\nCould you please send me some photos of your references + a list of clients?\r\nI need to understand quickly what the budget would be approximately. Our budget is limited to 600 ~ 800 aed/meter.\r\n\r\nAt your disposal to exchange by phone asap.\r\n\r\nBest regards,', '/exhibition-stand-builders-in-dubai/', '2023-12-06 17:35:55', '2023-12-06 17:35:55', '2.48.62.248'),
