(2725, 'Giovanni Polidori', 'SISTEMI srl', 'marketing@sistemiklein.com', '(+39) 0721 289525', 'LIGNA 2025', 'Hannover', '11x5 = 55 m²', NULL, '1', 'I am Giovanni Polidori from the Marketing Team of SISTEMI Klein - www.sistemiklein.com. A company that has been producing tools for the wood industry and not only for over 30 years. We will be exhibiting at LIGNA 2025 in Hannover - World market place of innovations for the wood industry - exhibition from May 26 to 30. \r\nI would like to receive an email contact to discuss the booth design and quote for LIGNA 2025. Budget: about 11,000 €.  Stand: 11x5 = 55 m²\r\nPhoto Stand and Plan Stand 2023 - to give you an idea. We actually did NOT like the Stand design this way very much. The panels that made up the booth were poorly constructed, the measurements were wrong, and the management was not optimal.\r\n•	LIGNA 2025 Map with the measure of our stand.\r\n•	List with our needs and requests. (list here in the email)\r\nLIST\r\n•	Stand: E86 – 11x5 = 55 m²\r\n•	Center column, 51 cm diameter + see measurements in attachments. We would like to cover the column and try to “enhance this space” (please, propose a solution). Could this be useful as a set-up to keep on top the company logo?\r\n•	From the Stand Map you can see that the right side (the one towards the entrance) is “covered” by a wall of about 400 / 380 cm long – 3m high - that side is important because we have a small space to attract the attention of visitors entering.\r\n•	Inside: 3 desks, 4 chairs per desk white and solid, power socket for each desk, wastebasket and a small cabinet beside each one.\r\n•	 Storage room: must be at least 2.20 x 2.50m ; inside 3 or more interior structures of 5 shelves each (sturdy steel shelving) + refrigerator (small, we will put our coffee machine on it), coat rack and 3 folding chairs inside, + multiple “power strip” outlet for charging multiple devices or phones.\r\n•	Small living room with 1 coffee table and 4 armchairs not attached to sofa but all 4 divided (in one side of the booth). Must be a “relax” area where visitors can sit and wait.\r\n•	Dividing or display wall between the two areas, between desks and lounge. It does not have to be a wall, but something to give the idea of “division” between the two areas.\r\n•	3 areas of display with showcases that can be opened and locked. Consider the “usual” Machinery, Preset Leader LINK: https://www.sistemiklein.com/it/strumenti-di-misura/8742-pre-set-leader-plus.html  normal power socket is needed and does not consume much power.\r\n•	Top part of the Stand, we had chosen white light cubes with green logo to attract attention (see attachments). I would opt for another solution. Visible logo on top. We want people to see our logo from distance.\r\n•	No reticular structure with visible tubes\r\n•	No hanging display structure (costs to hang are too high)\r\n•	Floor: light gray moquette\r\n•	Screen about 40 inches, in the column could be a solution. Obviously you recommend the optimal size for the column.\r\n•	Good lighting with light points.', '/hannover-messe/', '2024-12-16 22:39:12', '2024-12-16 22:39:12', '2.33.5.170'),
