(2776, 'Carl Brooks', 'oemsecrets', 'carlb@oemsecrets.com', '07967 302010', 'Embedded World', 'Nuremburg', '52sqm', NULL, '1', 'We\'re currently in the process of finding a new stand builder for SPS (Munich), Electronica (Munich) and Embedded World (Nuremberg); the closest show being Embedded World on 11th March 2025. \r\n\r\nWe have a slightly unusual idea, so wanted to find out if you would be able to support us. \r\n\r\nWe run a free comparison site and use the shows (and a free bar) to promote our services. We currently own (and store / transport) all the furniture needed for the buil. We use a stand builder to assemble the walls, apply the printed graphics and lay the carpet. This is destroyed at the end of each show. \r\n\r\nWe\'re looking for a solution that would allow us to re-use assets for each show. I\'ve attached a concept image which shows how ideally we\'d like the stand to look. After the materials (panelling, flooring) to make the stand have been purchased, we\'d ideally like to keep them as well as storing and transporting for future shows, where they would be re-assambled (by yourselves).\r\n\r\nThe other aspect of the design are the screens; we\'re looking into using an LED matrix system to display a syncronised video. The concept shows three 1x5 and one 3x3 55\" screens however this could be reduced.\r\n\r\nIs this build something you\'d be able to assist us with?\r\n\r\nThanks. Kind regards,\r\nCarl', '/', '2025-01-06 22:49:30', '2025-01-06 22:49:30', '193.186.4.64'),
